## Summary
Implemented a configurable Actor-Critic loop that replaces single-shot worker output with iterative refinement. The Actor (qwen3:30b-a3b) drafts content, the Critic (gemma3:12b) reviews with structured JSON feedback, and the Actor revises based on critique for up to 2 turns. Includes early termination when draft quality score ≥9, error handling for failed Critic calls, and maintains all existing Supervisor gate functionality. The loop prints clear turn-by-turn feedback to console while preserving the original output format and file structure.
